				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm pretty sure the EXT pins are always inputs. In a stock SNES, /MASTER on PPU1 is tied low and the PPU2 EXT pins are inputs (for Mode 7 EXTBG).<br /><br />/MASTER probably determines how sync timing is generated--whether to generate it inside the PPU or to let external logic drive it, presumably via the /EXTSYNC pin.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

